method.name: GetDirection

method.abstract: Get the Father Functioanl Flow Reference of the Functional Data Connection Point.

class.name: CATFctDeleteServices
class.abstract: Class providing services enabling deletion of Functional PLM Components from database.

method.abstract: Deletes a set of Functional References from database.

class.name: CATFctDirection
class.abstract: Possible directions for Functional Object (like Port or FlowExpositionInstance.

class.name: CATFctFactoriesProvider
class.abstract: Class providing access to factories related to Functional Partition.

method.name: GetReferenceFactory
method.abstract: Returns a factory allowing to create Functional References.

method.abstract: Returns a factory allowing to create Functional Representation References.

class.name: CATIFct2DPictureRepReference
class.abstract: Interface designating a Functional 2D Picture Representation Reference.

method.name: UpdatePicture
method.abstract: Updates the picture contained by the 2D Picture Representation Reference.

class.name: CATIFct2DPictures
class.abstract: Interface dedicated to Functional 2D Pictures collection management.

method.name: Associate2DPicture
method.abstract: Associates a 2D Picture to a Functional Reference.

method.name: CountAssociated2DPictures
method.abstract: Retrieves the number of 2D Pictures associated to this Functional Reference.

method.name: GetAssociated2DPictures
method.abstract: Retrieves the collection of 2D Pictures associated to this Functional Reference.

method.name: RemoveAssociated2DPicture
method.abstract: Removes a 2D Picture that is associated to this Functional Reference.

class.name: CATIFctConnectable
class.abstract: Interface dedicated to Functional systems connectivity management.

class.name: CATIFctConnection
class.abstract: Interface designating a Functional Connection.

method.name: GetConnectedElements
method.abstract: Retrieves the Functional Elements pointed by this Functional Connection.

method.name: GetConnectedElements
method.abstract: Retrieves the Functional Elements pointed by this Functional Connection.

method.name: GetParent
method.abstract: Retrieves the Functional Reference aggregating this Functional Connection.

class.name: CATIFctConnections
class.abstract: Interface dedicated to Functional Connections management.

method.name: Count
method.abstract: Retrieves the number of Functional Connections aggregated by this Functional Reference.

method.name: List
method.abstract: Retrieves the collection of connections aggregated by this Functional Reference.

method.name: Remove
method.abstract: Removes the given Functional Connection.

class.name: CATIFctFlowExpositionInstance
class.abstract: Interface dedicated to Functional Flow Exposition instance management.

method.name: GetDirection
method.abstract: Retrieves the instance direction.

method.name: GetFlowReference
method.abstract: Returns the flow reference which the flow instance comes from.

method.name: GetIdentifier
method.abstract: Retrieves the instance identifier.

method.name: GetOwner
method.abstract: Retrieves the reference which aggregates the instance.

method.name: SetDirection
method.abstract: Sets the instance direction.

class.name: CATIFctFlowExpositionInstances
class.abstract:
Interface dedicated to manage the collections of Functional Flow Exposition Instances aggregated by a Logical Reference
Role: This interface provides means to create, list or remove Functional Flow Exposition Instances aggregated by a Functional Reference.

class.name: CATIFctFlowInstance
class.abstract: Interface designating a Functional Flow Instance.

method.name: GetIdentifier
method.abstract: Retrieves the instance identifier.

method.name: GetReferenceInstanceOf
method.abstract: Retrieves the Functional Flow Reference this Functional Flow Instance comes from.

class.name: CATIFctFlowReference
class.abstract: Interface dedicated to Functional Flow Reference.

method.name: AddSubFlow
method.abstract: Adds a (Functional) Subflow to this Functional Flow.

method.name: CountSubFlows
method.abstract: Retrieves the number of subflows.

method.name: ListSubFlows
method.abstract: Lists the subflows of this Functional Flow.

method.name: RemoveSubFlow
method.abstract: Removes a subflow from this Functional Flow.

class.name: CATIFctInstance
class.abstract: Interface designating a Functional Instance.

method.name: Connect
method.abstract: Connects two instances of Functional systems together.

method.name: GetConnectedParentPorts
method.abstract: Retrieves the Functional Ports exposing at the upper level a specific port of this instance of Functional system.

method.name: GetConnectedSiblingSystems
method.abstract: Retrieves the instances of sibling Functional systems connected to this instance of Functional system.

method.name: GetFather
method.abstract: Retrieves the Functional Reference which aggregates this Functional Instance.

method.name: GetReferenceInstanceOf
method.abstract: Retrieves the instanciated Functional Reference.

class.name: CATIFctInstances
class.abstract: Interface dedicated to Functional Instances management.

method.name: Add
method.abstract: Instantiates a Functional Reference under this Functional Reference.

method.name: Count
method.abstract: Retrieves the number of Functional Instances aggregated by this Functional Reference.

method.name: List
method.abstract: Retrieves the collection of instances aggregated by this Functional Reference.

method.name: Remove
method.abstract: Removes the given instance that is aggregated by this Functional Reference.

class.name: CATIFctMuxDemuxReference
class.abstract: Interface designating a Functional Mux/Demux Reference.

method.name: GetFlow
method.abstract: Retrieves the structured flow associated to the Mux/Demux Reference.

method.name: GetKind
method.abstract: Retrieves the kind of Mux/Demux Reference.

method.name: GetPortFromSubFlow
method.abstract: Retrieves the Functional Port corresponding to a subflow of the structured flow associated to the Mux/Demux Reference.

method.name: ListPorts
method.abstract: Lists the ports of the Mux/Demux Reference.

enum.name: CommunicationType
enum.abstract: Defines the kind of Mux/Demux Reference.

class.name: CATIFctPort
class.abstract: Interface designating a Functional Port and providing means to manage the Functional Port properties.

method.name: Connect
method.abstract: Connects this Functional Port (of a Functional system) to an instance of Functional subsystem through a specific port.

method.name: GetConnectedSubSystems
method.abstract: Retrieves the instances of Functional subsystems connected to this Functional Port.

method.name: GetDirection
method.abstract: Retrieves the direction of this Functional Port.

method.name: GetFlow
method.abstract: Retrieves the Functional Flow Reference associated to this Functional Port.

method.name: GetFlowInstance
method.abstract: Retrieves the Functional Flow Instance associated to this Functional Port.

method.name: GetParent
method.abstract: Retrieves the Functional Reference aggregating this Functional Port.

method.name: RemoveFlow
method.abstract: Removes the Functional Flow associated to this Functional Port.

method.name: SetDirection
method.abstract: Sets the direction of this Functional Port.

method.name: SetFlow
method.abstract: Sets the Functional Flow associated to this Functional Port.

enum.name: PortDirection
enum.abstract: Defines the direction of a Functional Port.

class.name: CATIFctPorts
class.abstract: Interface dedicated to Functional Ports management.

method.name: Add
method.abstract: Creates a Functional Port.

method.name: Count
method.abstract: Retrieves the number of Functional Ports aggregated by this Functional Reference.

method.name: List
method.abstract: Retrieves the collection of Functional Ports aggregated by this Functional Reference.

method.name: Remove
method.abstract: Removes the given Functional Port.

class.name: CATIFctRepReferenceNonCATIAContent

method.name: CheckOut
method.abstract: Exports the stream associated to this Functional Representation Reference in the file system.

class.name: CATIFctRepresentationInstance
class.abstract: Interface designating a Functional Representation Instance.

method.name: GetParent
method.abstract: Retrieves the Functional Reference aggregating this Functional Representation Reference.

method.name: GetRepReferenceInstanceOf
method.abstract: Retrieves the Functional Representation Reference this Functional Representation Instance comes from.

class.name: CATIFctRepresentationInstances
class.abstract: Interface dedicated to manage the collections of Functional Representation Instances aggregated by a Functional Reference.

method.name: Add
method.abstract: Instantiates a Functional Representation Reference under this Functional Reference.

method.name: Count
method.abstract: Retrieves the number of Functional Representation Instances aggregated by this Functional Reference.

method.name: List
method.abstract: Lists the collection of Functional Representation Instances aggregated by this Functional Reference.

method.name: Remove
method.abstract: Removes the given Functional Representation Instance that is aggregated by this Functional Reference.

class.abstract: Interface designating a Functional Representation Reference.

method.name: IsOnceInstantiable
method.abstract: Checks if this Functional Representation Reference is once instantiable or not.

class.abstract: Interface to create Functional Representation References objects.

method.name: CreateWith2DPicture
method.abstract: Creates a Functional 2D Picture Representation Reference.

method.abstract: Creates a multi-instantiable Functional Non DSContent Representation Reference with a non CATIA stream.

method.abstract: Removes the given Functional Representation Reference that is aggregated by this Functional Reference.
